data.current_description: Returns a list of transactions for an account holder's accounts. You can specify the accounts and transaction statuses to be included on the list. The call returns a maximum of 50 transactions for each account. To retrieve all transactions, you must make another call with the 'page' value incremented. Transactions are listed in chronological order, with the most recent transaction first.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve paginated transaction history for account holder
data.description_suggestion: Returns a paginated list of transactions for an account holder's accounts. Supports filtering by specific accounts and transaction statuses. Each response returns a maximum of 50 transactions per account; use the 'page' parameter to retrieve additional transactions. Transactions are sorted chronologically with the most recent first. Requires AccountHolderTransactionListRequest with account and status filters.
data.reasoning: Original summary is too generic. Description lacks clarity about pagination requirements and input parameters needed for filtering. Enhanced version specifies pagination mechanism, filtering capabilities, and required request structure to help AI agents understand when and how to use this operation for transaction retrieval.

message: Operation 'post-debitAccountHolder' has semantic quality issues: missing_side_effects, missing_output_details. Summary is appropriate. Description needs clarification about asynchronous processing and the distinction between immediate response and webhook notification. Enhanced version explicitly states that settlement is asynchronous and clarifies the two-stage response mechanism (immediate response + webhook), which is critical for AI agents to understand the operation's side effects and timing.

data.current_description:
Sends a direct debit request to an account holder's bank account. If the direct debit is successful, the funds are settled in the accounts specified in the split instructions. Adyen sends the result of the direct debit in a [`DIRECT_DEBIT_INITIATED`](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/#/NotificationService/latest/post/DIRECT_DEBIT_INITIATED) notification webhook.

 To learn more about direct debits, see [Top up accounts](https://docs.adyen.com/classic-platforms/top-up-accounts).
data.description_suggestion: Initiates a direct debit request from an account holder's bank account to fund platform accounts. Upon successful processing, funds are distributed to accounts according to specified split instructions. The operation returns an immediate response with the debit status, and Adyen sends a DIRECT_DEBIT_INITIATED webhook notification with the final result. Note that actual fund settlement occurs asynchronously via the webhook notification.
data.reasoning: Summary is appropriate. Description needs clarification about asynchronous processing and the distinction between immediate response and webhook notification. Enhanced version explicitly states that settlement is asynchronous and clarifies the two-stage response mechanism (immediate response + webhook), which is critical for AI agents to understand the operation's side effects and timing.

data.current_summary: Designate a beneficiary account and transfer the benefactor's current balance
data.current_description: Defines a benefactor and a beneficiary relationship between two accounts. At the time of benefactor/beneficiary setup, the funds in the benefactor account are transferred to the beneficiary account, and any further payments to the benefactor account are automatically sent to the beneficiary account. A series of benefactor/beneficiaries may not exceed four beneficiaries and may not have a cycle in it.
data.description_suggestion: Establishes a benefactor-beneficiary relationship between two accounts, automatically redirecting all current and future funds from the benefactor account to the beneficiary account. At setup, the benefactor's current balance is immediately transferred to the beneficiary. Beneficiary chains are limited to a maximum of four levels and cannot contain cycles. Requires both account identifiers. Returns confirmation of the established relationship and the transferred amount.
data.reasoning: Summary is clear but description lacks input requirements and output details.
